17	https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/clay-culture-carbon-meet-the-makers-tickets-1428552812919?aff=ebdssbdestsearch	event-bright	Title: Clay | Culture | Carbon: 'Meet The Makers'\\nShort Description: Explore the Clay | Culture | Carbon exhibition after hours and meet the makers, collaborators, and curators behind it.\\nLocation: Morris + Company 215 Mare Street London E8 3QJ United Kingdom\\nCost: Donation\\nDates: Thursday, July 10 · 6 - 9pm GMT+1\\nDescription: As part of our on-going Clay | Culture | Carbon event programme, we invite you to “Meet The Makers” at a special Studio Late, an evening to explore the exhibition after hours and meet the makers, collaborators, and curators behind it. At the heart of the show is a series of co-created installations that explore clay as a medium of carbon, culture, and collaboration, from found materials to regenerative making, and from site-sourced earth to reimagined bricks.___You’ll hear directly from those who shaped the exhibition’s craft-focused, research-led, and community-rooted approach, in conversation with exhibition curator Elly Ward Morris. We'll discuss 'co-making' principles with our Head of Sustainability, David Storring, and Edie Parfitt from CELLA, the young makers collective who designed and built the central installation:Then we'll hear more about two alternatives to carbon-intensive fired-clay brick production: Earth bricks presented by Laura Marcheggiano from Arup's Materials Team, and 'Circulabrick' presented by Dave Mills of Lyons & Annoot. Finally, we'll take a detailed look at the beautiful work of 'Hackney Potter' Adele Williams, who forages raw clay to make experimental clay bodies and slips, ashes for glazing and firing techniques in her practice. ___The exhibition is part of a wider exploration into clay as both a building material and tool, asking how it might shape more inclusive, sustainable futures.This Studio Late is a chance to meet the people behind the ideas, hear the stories that shaped the work, and reflect on how architecture can respond to today’s material and environmental urgencies, with clay at the centre.___Tickets are free with a donation to our local charity partners Made In Hackney.	Clay | Culture | Carbon: 'Meet The Makers'	Explore the innovative Clay | Culture | Carbon exhibition and engage directly with the visionary makers, collaborators, and curators behind it. This special Studio Late event takes place on 10 July 2024.	Explore the innovative Clay | Culture | Carbon exhibition and engage directly with the visionary makers, collaborators, and curators behind it.	Join us for a unique 'Meet The Makers' Studio Late event, offering an exclusive after-hours exploration of the 'Clay | Culture | Carbon' exhibition. This special evening is designed to connect you directly with the creative minds, dedicated collaborators, and insightful curators who brought this compelling show to life. Discover how the exhibition delves into clay as a multifaceted medium, exploring its role in carbon sequestration, its cultural significance, and the power of collaborative making.\n\nGain direct insights into the exhibition’s craft-focused, research-led, and community-rooted methodologies through engaging conversations. You'll hear from exhibition curator Elly Ward Morris, and learn about 'co-making' principles with David Storring, Head of Sustainability, and Edie Parfitt from CELLA, the collective behind the central installation. The event will also feature discussions on low-carbon alternatives to traditional fired bricks, including Earth bricks from Arup's Materials Team and 'Circulabrick' by Lyons & Annoot. Furthermore, discover the fascinating work of 'Hackney Potter' Adele Williams, who masterfully transforms foraged raw clay into experimental pieces.\n\nThis event offers a valuable opportunity to understand how architecture can effectively respond to pressing material and environmental challenges by embracing sustainable practices with clay. It's especial